Generate mesh

$ gmsh -2 naca0012.geo

Convert to rea

$ python naca0012.py

Run genmap and enter some tolerance, e.g., 0.01

$ genmap

Compile nek

$ makenek naca0012

Run nek, e.g., using 4 processor mpi

$ nekbmpi naca0012 4

You can look into log file for the progress

$ tail -f naca0012.log.4

Solution is saved periodically. You can visualize using visit.

$ visnek naca0012
$ visit (open the naca0012.nek5000 file)

Vorticity is saved in the temperature variable

To compute frequencies from force history

$ grep drag naca0012.log.4 > clcd.txt

Then run get_freq.m in matlab.
